[normal]BPS is the primary UK learned society concerned with research into drugs and the way they work. Our members work in a
[normal]cademia, industry, and the health services, and many are medically qualified. The Society covers the whole spectrum of pharmacology, including laboratory, clinical, toxicological and regulatory aspects. 
[normal]Clinic
[normal]al pharmacology is the medical speciality
[normal] dedi
[normal]cated to promoting safe and effective use of medicines for patient benefit. Clinical pharmacologists work as consultants in the NHS and many hold prominent positions in UK Universities.
